x4freetext: The experiment was carried out at the
Cyclotron Department of the NRCAM in Karaj.
Uniform targets of 209-Bi and 197-Au were prepared by
vacuum evaporation. The 209-Bi target consisted of a
570 mug/cm2 deposit of the element evaporated onto
40 mug/cm2 carbon backing, while the 197-Au target was
thickness of the targets were determined by Rutherford
back scattering, and the targets were analyzed by PIXE.
The results showed that no fissionable impurities were
The fission fragments were detected with two
The active area of the detectors were 300 and 100 mm2,
The intensity of the beam was limited to 100 nA
to prevent pile-up and saturation effects in the
detectors.  The collected charge for bombardment of
bismuth and gold were 280 and 1200 muC, respectively.
